do, I am reasonably sure that <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">American</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">governments</ENAMEX> of the <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">1990s</NUMEX> cannot do, nor
would I wish it. I merely predict that sometime in <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">the coming generation</TIMEX>,
<ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">profanity</ENAMEX> will return in a meaningful way. It served too many purposes for too
many years of <ENAMEX TYPE="NATIONALITY">American</ENAMEX> life to disappear on a permanent basis. We need it.

